HEADWORD: Occipito-
<hw>Oc*cip"i*to-</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[See <er>Occiput</er>.]</ety>
<def>A combining form denoting <sig>relation to the occiput</sig>, or
<sig>situation near the occiput</sig>; <as>as, <ex>occipito</ex>-axial;
<ex>occipito</ex>-mastoid.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

